==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ureameter
<hw>U`re*am"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Urea</ets>
+ <ets>-meter</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol. Chem.)</fld> <def>An
apparatus for the determination of the amount of urea in urine, in which
the nitrogen evolved by the action of certain reagents, on a given
volume of urine, is collected and measured, and the urea calculated
accordingly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Urechitin</ent>⟦br⟧
